WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:13.742 --> 00:00:15.642
Find out that man's name.

3
00:00:20.750 --> 00:00:24.186
I have come to visit Robin of Locksley.
but find him not at home.

4
00:00:25.255 --> 00:00:28.588
Perhaps one of you would like to inform
me of his whereabouts.

5
00:00:28.658 --> 00:00:31.822
He and I need to have a little chat.
a conversation.

6
00:00:33.096 --> 00:00:34.461
Nobody knows.

7
00:00:35.266 --> 00:00:37.757
Nobody knows.

8
00:00:37.835 --> 00:00:40.531
Then... there is a reward.

9
00:00:40.604 --> 00:00:43.072
Shall we say... 20 pounds?

10
00:00:45.010 --> 00:00:48.069
And then all of a sudden somebody does know.

11
00:00:48.146 --> 00:00:50.580
Loosen your tongues or lose your tongues!

12
00:01:01.527 --> 00:01:03.154
Cut out his tongue...

13
00:01:03.229 --> 00:01:06.357
One an hour until somebody talks.

14
00:01:07.633 --> 00:01:08.600
(Screams)

15
00:02:00.890 --> 00:02:03.586
- You're making a mistake.
- What?

16
00:02:03.660 --> 00:02:06.527
You're gonna send an army to hunt us down.
tear us limb from limb?

17
00:02:06.596 --> 00:02:08.996
You think we're frightened of the Sheriff?
Are we?

18
00:02:09.065 --> 00:02:12.433
- No.
- No. we are also against the Sheriff.

19
00:02:12.503 --> 00:02:16.099
- What do you want. a medal?
- We should be on the same side.

20
00:02:16.174 --> 00:02:17.800
Master. tell him.

21
00:02:21.713 --> 00:02:24.045
That rabbit is not...

22
00:02:24.116 --> 00:02:26.710
I think you'll find that rabbit is not yet cooked.

23
00:02:26.785 --> 00:02:29.380
- I think you'll find he eats them raw.
- Raw?!

24
00:02:30.922 --> 00:02:34.086
- Is that wise? I mean. that is dangerous.
- Oh!

25
00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:36.185
Will you just shut up?

26
00:02:36.262 --> 00:02:37.957
- You're a noble?
- Yes...

27
00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:42.831
...and no.

28
00:02:42.902 --> 00:02:44.928
Smells like one.

29
00:02:45.005 --> 00:02:46.904
Smells lovely.

30
00:02:47.675 --> 00:02:49.107
Flowers. Lavender.

31
00:02:49.175 --> 00:02:51.167
- Rose petals.
- What?

32
00:02:51.245 --> 00:02:55.204
You rub it on. did you. lavender balm?
Yeah. you smell too.

33
00:02:55.282 --> 00:02:58.343
No. I had a bath.
He washed in rose petals.

34
00:02:58.420 --> 00:03:03.824
And they reckon they're same side as us.
You know any outlaws who take lavender baths?

35
00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:05.723
No! John?

36
00:03:05.794 --> 00:03:07.421
It's not lavender.

37
00:03:08.997 --> 00:03:10.590
All right.

38
00:03:12.768 --> 00:03:14.167
Got a ha'penny here. John!

39
00:03:15.071 --> 00:03:17.767
You have the horses. leave him his ha'penny.

40
00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:19.569
How come you got no purse?

41
00:03:19.642 --> 00:03:22.110
Because I was not planning on
coming to the woods.

42
00:03:22.178 --> 00:03:23.874
- Is this what you do?
- What?

43
00:03:23.947 --> 00:03:26.744
- Stealing willy-nilly.
- Stealing willy-nilly?

44
00:03:26.816 --> 00:03:29.148
I can't understand what he's saying. Can you?

45
00:03:29.218 --> 00:03:31.710
Do you care who you steal from?

46
00:03:31.788 --> 00:03:35.884
My friend here has but a ha'penny.
What you take from him might be all he has.

47
00:03:35.959 --> 00:03:38.894
- Yeah. it is all I have.
- Heartbreaking. Do we care?

48
00:03:40.531 --> 00:03:44.331
- We don't care.
- We're dead men. Think about it... outlaws.

49
00:03:44.402 --> 00:03:46.028
Oh. that is sophisticated.

50
00:03:46.904 --> 00:03:49.270
Oh. big words. Scary.

51
00:03:49.340 --> 00:03:51.069
(Whistles)

52
00:04:07.860 --> 00:04:09.293
Those were horrible men.

53
00:04:09.361 --> 00:04:13.059
They could have left us here to die
for all they care.

54
00:04:13.133 --> 00:04:17.194
If they had not taken our weapons. I'd say we
should go after them and give them a hiding.

55
00:04:17.271 --> 00:04:19.101
A hiding to remember.

56
00:04:21.008 --> 00:04:22.599
But...

57
00:04:23.676 --> 00:04:25.076
you.

58
00:04:26.981 --> 00:04:29.108
You let me think...

59
00:04:31.887 --> 00:04:36.256
- You freed yourself. why did you not fight?
- Erm...

60
00:04:36.324 --> 00:04:37.848
I thought it best to wait.

61
00:04:37.926 --> 00:04:39.894
Why?

62
00:04:39.961 --> 00:04:45.298
Because. Much. you were right.
We should teach them a lesson.

63
00:04:45.368 --> 00:04:46.335
Gentlemen!

64
00:04:48.571 --> 00:04:50.004
Oh. no!

65
00:04:51.073 --> 00:04:52.904
Master. surely...

66
00:04:53.576 --> 00:04:54.736
(Robin chuckles)

67
00:04:55.078 --> 00:04:58.069
Yeah. Let's go.

68
00:04:58.147 --> 00:04:59.547
Tick-tock.

69
00:05:00.617 --> 00:05:02.209
Tick-tock.

70
00:05:10.127 --> 00:05:12.493
Have I told you that I can't taste wine?

71
00:05:12.563 --> 00:05:15.055
Have the best. of course...

72
00:05:15.133 --> 00:05:17.191
but I don't have the palate for it.

73
00:05:27.379 --> 00:05:29.278
(Laughter)

74
00:05:30.616 --> 00:05:32.880
Yeah? What about a hat?

75
00:05:32.952 --> 00:05:34.647
Oh. yeah. yeah.

76
00:05:37.656 --> 00:05:40.284
I think your find that's not properly cooked.

77
00:05:53.406 --> 00:05:55.375
This is our forest too.

78
00:05:55.443 --> 00:05:57.205
I think you'll find.

79
00:06:02.216 --> 00:06:03.877
Take your clothes off.

80
00:06:09.958 --> 00:06:11.425
Robin!

81
00:06:12.995 --> 00:06:15.930
Aaagh! Aaaaghh!

82
00:06:18.768 --> 00:06:20.394
This is unacceptable.

83
00:06:21.370 --> 00:06:22.803
The master will...

84
00:06:22.871 --> 00:06:24.567
When this dispute is resolved.

85
00:06:24.641 --> 00:06:26.302
Robin will return. he will.

86
00:06:26.376 --> 00:06:28.606
Robin. he'll never be master of anywhere now.

87
00:06:28.678 --> 00:06:30.111
Master of Sherwood. maybe.

88
00:06:30.179 --> 00:06:32.613
- Robin of the wood.
- I like that. Robin of the wood.

89
00:06:32.682 --> 00:06:34.946
- Robin Wood?
- (Laughs)

90
00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:38.688
- Guy would like that.
- You should tell him.

91
00:06:38.756 --> 00:06:41.281
- You tell him.
- I'm not gonna tell him. He might not like it.

92
00:06:41.992 --> 00:06:44.859
You are revolting. You know that?

93
00:06:45.963 --> 00:06:49.296
My master and I fought for five years
in the Holy Land.

94
00:06:49.366 --> 00:06:51.335
For what?

95
00:06:52.404 --> 00:06:54.463
So that people like you could run amok

96
00:06:55.540 --> 00:07:01.138
with your lawlessness
and your disgusting camp and your snide...

97
00:07:02.181 --> 00:07:04.172
your snide...

98
00:07:04.250 --> 00:07:07.048
Your snide. your snide...?

99
00:07:08.087 --> 00:07:09.486
- Dance.
- You. what?

100
00:07:10.456 --> 00:07:12.617
- Dance.
- No way.

101
00:07:14.127 --> 00:07:15.253
Ow!

102
00:07:16.363 --> 00:07:17.921
Dance!

103
00:07:25.373 --> 00:07:28.809
Very good. like dancing bears.

104
00:07:28.876 --> 00:07:30.502
How does it feel?

105
00:07:31.579 --> 00:07:34.047
You treat your fellow man like an animal!

106
00:07:35.483 --> 00:07:36.916
How does it feel?

107
00:07:36.985 --> 00:07:40.012
You take from those worse off than yourselves
and leave them to die.

108
00:07:40.089 --> 00:07:41.954
All right. you've made your point.

109
00:07:42.024 --> 00:07:44.720
You're not Englishmen.

110
00:07:44.793 --> 00:07:47.091
You're not the England we fought for.

111
00:07:47.162 --> 00:07:49.723
Men who think it is a boast to be dead.

112
00:07:50.332 --> 00:07:52.233
What do you think you're doing robbing him.

113
00:07:52.301 --> 00:07:55.601
when the Sheriff over there
is robbing it all 20 times over?

114
00:07:57.874 --> 00:08:01.605
Skulking in the woods.
while he steals spirits and livelihoods.

115
00:08:01.678 --> 00:08:05.479
Why are you skulking in the woods?
What are you gonna do about it?

116
00:08:07.451 --> 00:08:09.543
Stop him.

117
00:08:11.155 --> 00:08:12.986
I'm going to stop him.

118
00:08:13.057 --> 00:08:16.754
Well. you can't stop a sheriff.

119
00:08:17.629 --> 00:08:20.358
Only the Crown can withdraw his license.

120
00:08:20.431 --> 00:08:23.230
When the King returns.
he will have his comeuppance.

121
00:08:23.301 --> 00:08:26.361
Until then. we will scupper
his sadistic punishments.

122
00:08:26.438 --> 00:08:30.272
We will stop his insane taxes and give them
back to the poor where they belong.

123
00:08:30.342 --> 00:08:32.810
- Sure.
- We will rob him.

124
00:08:34.213 --> 00:08:36.773
And if you dead men had had
spines in your backs...

125
00:08:36.849 --> 00:08:39.340
that's what you'd have been doing
for the last five years.

126
00:08:39.419 --> 00:08:41.080
Rousing. lavender boy.

127
00:08:41.154 --> 00:08:43.452
- Good luck.
- Yeah. see ya.

128
00:08:44.324 --> 00:08:46.917
That'd be a mistake. I think you'll find.

129
00:08:48.929 --> 00:08:51.227
(Bird screeches)

130
00:08:59.908 --> 00:09:03.674
You are in no position to argue...

131
00:09:03.745 --> 00:09:05.736
dunderhead!

132
00:09:13.255 --> 00:09:14.812
Oh!

133
00:09:17.392 --> 00:09:20.556
Look. you've tied us up. we've tied you up.

134
00:09:20.629 --> 00:09:24.498
We could call it quits.
We could all be on our way.

135
00:09:25.835 --> 00:09:26.803
Him...

136
00:09:26.870 --> 00:09:28.530
- I do not like.
- It is mutual.

137
00:09:30.673 --> 00:09:31.698
(Whispers)

138
00:09:32.709 --> 00:09:35.177
Are you Robin of Locksley?

139
00:09:35.245 --> 00:09:37.840
Robin. Earl of Huntingdon.

140
00:09:39.817 --> 00:09:41.307
Good.

141
00:09:42.687 --> 00:09:43.914
(Church bells chiming)

142
00:09:43.987 --> 00:09:45.353
Another hour.

143
00:09:46.657 --> 00:09:48.386
This is not necessary. Where is Robin?

144
00:09:50.228 --> 00:09:51.195
Talk!

145
00:09:53.098 --> 00:09:55.464
He will never be your master again.

146
00:09:56.367 --> 00:10:00.031
You need have no fear of reprisals from him.
I'm your master now.

147
00:10:00.105 --> 00:10:01.072
For good.

148
00:10:02.574 --> 00:10:05.065
(Much) At least have the courtesy to untie him.

149
00:10:08.447 --> 00:10:11.542
Locksley? You brought us home.

150
00:10:11.618 --> 00:10:15.076
- It seems there may be a reward.
- 20 pounds.

151
00:10:15.155 --> 00:10:17.681
Take him down. See if we can
get summat for this rabble too.

152
00:10:18.324 --> 00:10:21.226
- Me? I'm supposed to be dead.
- Me too. they won't recognize you.

153
00:10:21.295 --> 00:10:23.490
Well. if they do. I'll be hanged.

154
00:10:23.564 --> 00:10:25.725
- John?
- John can't go. can he?

155
00:10:25.799 --> 00:10:28.427
If they're gonna recognize anyone.
it's gonna be John.

156
00:10:28.502 --> 00:10:30.402
We all go.

157
00:10:31.238 --> 00:10:33.900
It is unfortunate.

158
00:10:33.974 --> 00:10:36.306
A man goes to war.

159
00:10:36.377 --> 00:10:40.007
his spirit can be damaged.
his vision blurred.

160
00:10:40.081 --> 00:10:42.606
his understanding of law and order.

161
00:10:42.684 --> 00:10:45.949
This is what has happened to Robin.

162
00:10:46.021 --> 00:10:49.981
I have heard that
there are camps in the Holy Land

163
00:10:51.260 --> 00:10:54.923
where men are taught to hate their own land.

164
00:10:54.997 --> 00:10:58.592
to return home to wreak
havoc and destruction.

165
00:10:58.668 --> 00:11:02.469
Maybe this is what has happened to Robin.
we don't know. But what we do know...

166
00:11:02.539 --> 00:11:07.067
is that by his actions in Nottingham.

167
00:11:07.144 --> 00:11:11.241
your former master. did not. as some of
the romantics amongst you might believe.

168
00:11:11.315 --> 00:11:13.307
strike a blow for freedom.

169
00:11:14.419 --> 00:11:16.011
Make no mistake about it.

170
00:11:16.087 --> 00:11:18.646
He perverted the course of justice.

171
00:11:18.723 --> 00:11:23.184
and in so doing.
he attacked the very fabric of our state.

172
00:11:24.563 --> 00:11:27.224
The state that we all work for.

173
00:11:27.298 --> 00:11:30.427
the state that we all pay our taxes for.

174
00:11:35.107 --> 00:11:37.132
He would rob us of that.

175
00:11:38.177 --> 00:11:40.169
Of our taxes. of our hard work.

176
00:11:52.260 --> 00:11:53.817
Another tongue. I suppose.

177
00:11:57.464 --> 00:12:01.925
No. no. no. no!

178
00:12:02.003 --> 00:12:04.836
- Oh. God! No!
- No!

179
00:12:04.905 --> 00:12:07.841
That is nasty... and that is brutish.

180
00:12:07.909 --> 00:12:09.376
- That is Alice.
- Alice?

181
00:12:09.444 --> 00:12:11.412
- My wife.
- You're Alice's John?

182
00:12:11.480 --> 00:12:12.640
She thought you were dead.

183
00:12:13.649 --> 00:12:15.550
It's you they want. we go now.

184
00:12:16.251 --> 00:12:18.151
(Robin) You can't. you'll hang.

185
00:12:18.220 --> 00:12:20.688
There is no time. I can save your wife.

186
00:12:20.756 --> 00:12:22.520
Put me down.

187
00:12:24.727 --> 00:12:26.752
Untie me. My bow. quickly.

188
00:12:26.829 --> 00:12:29.423
- (Alice cries out)
- I am good with a bow.

189
00:12:29.499 --> 00:12:31.558
- You saw him shoot your feet.
- Trust me.

190
00:12:46.317 --> 00:12:48.410
He's here.

191
00:12:48.887 --> 00:12:50.081
Find him.

192
00:12:50.155 --> 00:12:52.088
- Let's go.
- Godspeed.

193
00:12:52.757 --> 00:12:54.156
What?

194
00:12:54.225 --> 00:12:56.455
You have served me well. my friend.

195
00:12:56.528 --> 00:12:58.895
And I have led you to this.

196
00:12:58.964 --> 00:13:00.555
- Apologies.
- No.

197
00:13:00.632 --> 00:13:03.397
Go. I will find a way through this.

198
00:13:04.403 --> 00:13:06.337
- The Sheriff will hang you.
- If he does.

199
00:13:06.405 --> 00:13:08.430
at least I will not die a dead man.

200
00:13:13.879 --> 00:13:17.407
Good scheme. Sheriff. Very effective.

201
00:13:17.483 --> 00:13:19.645
Impressive logic.

202
00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:22.246
Now. I wonder.

203
00:13:23.256 --> 00:13:25.521
If I tell you where I am.

204
00:13:25.593 --> 00:13:28.027
can I claim the 20 pounds?

205
00:13:28.096 --> 00:13:31.065
That would be a pound or so
for each family here.

206
00:13:33.301 --> 00:13:35.132
Eat a whole winter off that.

207
00:13:35.203 --> 00:13:36.865
Amusing.

208
00:13:36.938 --> 00:13:38.907
Put down your weapon.
you're surrounded.

209
00:13:38.974 --> 00:13:41.101
I am Guy of Gisborne.

210
00:13:41.176 --> 00:13:43.838
the new lord of this manor
and soon to be Earl of Huntingdon.

211
00:13:44.847 --> 00:13:48.180
Your presence here is no longer required.
Put down your weapon.

212
00:14:18.749 --> 00:14:20.717
That was a cruel game to play.

213
00:14:22.888 --> 00:14:24.651
Game?

214
00:14:26.725 --> 00:14:28.317
You don't understand.

215
00:14:28.393 --> 00:14:31.692
You do not play games with me.

216
00:14:34.399 --> 00:14:36.458
You made a mistake in Nottingham.

217
00:14:36.535 --> 00:14:40.097
Hm? Trying to be the peasants' hero.

218
00:14:40.173 --> 00:14:43.142
Well. why don't you be the peasants' hero
and show me how it's done?

219
00:14:43.209 --> 00:14:47.771
Oh. shall we have a meeting
in the morning to discuss it?

220
00:14:47.848 --> 00:14:49.678
A clue - no.

221
00:14:51.185 --> 00:14:53.016
In the morning...

222
00:14:53.086 --> 00:14:54.212
you shall hang.

223
00:14:59.726 --> 00:15:00.886
Aww.

224
00:15:00.961 --> 00:15:02.759
All hope lost.

225
00:15:08.203 --> 00:15:10.671
- I liked him.
- I did not.

226
00:15:10.738 --> 00:15:12.831
He saved your wife.

227
00:15:14.008 --> 00:15:15.977
"Liked"?

228
00:15:16.045 --> 00:15:17.739
He's not dead.

229
00:15:52.484 --> 00:15:53.815
Fool.

230
00:15:58.790 --> 00:16:01.088
Ah... Are we rich?

231
00:16:02.294 --> 00:16:04.489
- What's the matter?
- Saw his wife.

232
00:16:05.264 --> 00:16:07.664
- No reward?
- My master gave himself in.

233
00:16:07.733 --> 00:16:10.464
- To the Sheriff?
- The Sheriff was cutting out tongues.

234
00:16:11.571 --> 00:16:14.301
He could hardly stand by
and watch people lose their tongues.

235
00:16:14.374 --> 00:16:17.366
(Chuckles) That would be funny. wouldn't it?

236
00:16:17.443 --> 00:16:19.344
If instead of "Cat got your tongue?"

237
00:16:20.214 --> 00:16:21.976
They said. "Sheriff got your tongue?"

238
00:16:22.048 --> 00:16:23.539
What?

239
00:16:23.617 --> 00:16:28.179
If someone was a bit. you know. quiet.
you'd go. "What's the matter?

240
00:16:28.255 --> 00:16:30.281
"Sheriff got your tongue?"

241
00:16:33.495 --> 00:16:36.896
Look. we cannot just sit here.
We've got to do something.

242
00:16:36.965 --> 00:16:40.332
We've got to go to Nottingham
and we've got to... get him out.

243
00:16:40.402 --> 00:16:42.496
How?

244
00:16:42.571 --> 00:16:45.369
- No point anyway.
- No point?

245
00:16:45.440 --> 00:16:47.238
You would be dead if Robin had not...

246
00:16:47.310 --> 00:16:49.335
- That's true.
- You would be dead.

247
00:16:49.412 --> 00:16:53.872
Mind you. I weren't supposed to hang
in the first place. That was just a confusion.

248
00:16:53.950 --> 00:16:56.578
Look. you can't just let him die. Will?

249
00:17:03.660 --> 00:17:05.593
Very well.

250
00:17:05.661 --> 00:17:07.027
I shall go alone.

251
00:17:07.097 --> 00:17:08.155
See ya.

252
00:17:08.231 --> 00:17:10.200
Oi! Hold it. no horse.

253
00:17:26.085 --> 00:17:28.053
In which house is my wife?

254
00:17:28.120 --> 00:17:29.314
I will fetch her.

255
00:17:29.388 --> 00:17:31.184
- Fetch her where?
- Here.

256
00:17:31.255 --> 00:17:33.019
A woman can live in the forest same as us.

257
00:17:33.092 --> 00:17:36.493
- Alice can't live in the forest.
- Why not?

258
00:17:36.562 --> 00:17:39.053
Ah... there 's something you don't know.

259
00:17:46.539 --> 00:17:49.007
(Muffled screaming)

260
00:17:50.977 --> 00:17:53.309
Not so high and mighty now. are we?

261
00:17:55.282 --> 00:17:56.578
Oh!

262
00:17:56.650 --> 00:18:00.143
That's for the priest trick.
Could have cost me my job.

263
00:18:00.221 --> 00:18:01.916
One job to save four lives?

264
00:18:04.291 --> 00:18:07.125
Won't be saving anyone now. my lovely.
wherever you're from.

265
00:18:07.195 --> 00:18:09.254
He's not Robin of Locksley any more.

266
00:18:09.331 --> 00:18:12.266
Robin Wood. they're calling him.

267
00:18:12.333 --> 00:18:13.392
Robin Hood?

268
00:18:13.468 --> 00:18:16.437
There will be no hood for you tomorrow.
my lovely.

269
00:18:16.505 --> 00:18:19.565
The Sheriff wants the rebels
to see the fear in your eyes.

270
00:18:19.641 --> 00:18:22.475
He wants them to see your eyes pop right out.

271
00:18:42.199 --> 00:18:44.326
- Nothing?!
- What can I do?

272
00:18:44.401 --> 00:18:46.869
I warned him. the Sheriff.

273
00:18:46.938 --> 00:18:48.667
Yes. my Lord. but...

274
00:18:48.739 --> 00:18:51.538
He should have listened to my father.
now he is an outlaw.

275
00:18:51.609 --> 00:18:54.840
- I know. my Ladyship.
- And not a very impressive one.

276
00:18:54.913 --> 00:18:57.245
That is...

277
00:18:58.850 --> 00:19:00.284
Forgive me.

278
00:19:01.554 --> 00:19:05.547
That is not fair. he is most impressive.

279
00:19:05.624 --> 00:19:09.856
He is caught after just one day.
Does that impress you?

280
00:19:10.730 --> 00:19:13.825
He gave himself up to save tongues.

281
00:19:13.900 --> 00:19:16.663
- Tongues?
- In Locksley.

282
00:19:16.736 --> 00:19:21.538
The Sheriff was cutting out people's tongues
until somebody told him where Robin was.

283
00:19:22.543 --> 00:19:24.510
I hate the Sheriff...

284
00:19:27.081 --> 00:19:30.277
and I hate you.
if you aren't gonna help Robin.

285
00:19:31.284 --> 00:19:37.315
Young man. I will speak in court. of course.
but your master has doomed himself.

286
00:19:37.391 --> 00:19:39.723
His fate is...

287
00:19:39.794 --> 00:19:40.762
Resign yourself.

288
00:19:44.299 --> 00:19:47.063
In the Holy Land. my master had dreams.

289
00:19:49.071 --> 00:19:50.265
He spoke your name.

290
00:19:56.745 --> 00:19:58.213
Good night.

291
00:20:19.404 --> 00:20:21.200
(Whistles)

292
00:20:22.373 --> 00:20:24.103
Who are you?

293
00:20:24.176 --> 00:20:25.438
- Who are you?
- John.

294
00:20:25.510 --> 00:20:27.068
- John what?
- John Little.

295
00:20:27.145 --> 00:20:29.443
- Oh!
- But people call me Little John.

296
00:20:29.514 --> 00:20:31.540
- Do you know why?
- Why?

297
00:20:31.617 --> 00:20:34.517
Because my father was called John too.
John Little.

298
00:20:35.854 --> 00:20:39.291
He was a hero. He was big. I think.

299
00:20:39.358 --> 00:20:41.486
What's your name?

300
00:20:42.161 --> 00:20:43.628
I am...

301
00:20:45.032 --> 00:20:46.999
I'm a friend of your mother' s.

302
00:20:48.335 --> 00:20:51.998
- How is she?
- Always tired. always sewing.

303
00:20:52.072 --> 00:20:53.733
- But do you know what?
- What?

304
00:20:53.807 --> 00:20:58.177
Everything's gonna be better now
because Robin's back from the Holy Land.

305
00:20:58.246 --> 00:20:59.769
Oh?

306
00:20:59.847 --> 00:21:04.308
He always makes sure people have enough
to eat. I had a feast at the big house.

307
00:21:04.385 --> 00:21:07.218
and I had so much pork my belly ached.

308
00:21:07.989 --> 00:21:10.048
and Mother had fish. but...

309
00:21:10.124 --> 00:21:12.319
Eugh! Fish I do not like.

310
00:21:12.862 --> 00:21:14.955
F... Fish is her favorite.

311
00:21:15.563 --> 00:21:18.226
Robin will come back from Nottingham.

312
00:21:18.300 --> 00:21:20.097
- Won't he?
- I...

313
00:21:20.169 --> 00:21:21.932
(Alice) Little John!

314
00:21:23.205 --> 00:21:24.797
Where are you? Little John?

315
00:21:24.875 --> 00:21:28.173
- Do you want to come in?
- I don't think I can. Little John.

316
00:21:28.778 --> 00:21:30.712
(Alice) John!

317
00:21:30.780 --> 00:21:33.408
It's late. come on.

318
00:21:51.969 --> 00:21:53.698
I've realized something about you.

319
00:21:53.772 --> 00:21:55.239
I thought you didn't want to talk.

320
00:21:55.307 --> 00:21:58.435
- Mm. that was before I realized.
- Realized what?

321
00:21:58.510 --> 00:22:01.070
You are a renowned marksman with the bow.

322
00:22:01.146 --> 00:22:05.310
You saw me about to excise a tongue or two.
you could have shot me. why didn't you?

323
00:22:06.319 --> 00:22:09.584
You had men everywhere. I had only a few.

324
00:22:10.790 --> 00:22:14.921
- We were outnumbered.
- Yeah. well. that may be true.

325
00:22:14.994 --> 00:22:16.291
But...

326
00:22:17.730 --> 00:22:19.197
you gave yourself up.

327
00:22:19.265 --> 00:22:25.034
I care about those people. my people.
more than I care about myself.

328
00:22:25.105 --> 00:22:28.666
- You would not understand.
- Yeah. but that's not the point.

329
00:22:28.742 --> 00:22:30.972
- Do you want to know what the point is?
- No.

330
00:22:31.045 --> 00:22:35.176
The point is you care more about my life
than you do about your own.

331
00:22:37.986 --> 00:22:41.422
- No.
- Then why didn't you kill me?

332
00:22:41.489 --> 00:22:44.083
Surely you must have known
that I would see you executed.

333
00:22:45.894 --> 00:22:47.725
Have you lost your nerve?

334
00:22:48.564 --> 00:22:51.555
Have you lost your taste for blood? Hm?

335
00:22:51.634 --> 00:22:55.593
Robin of Locksley. honored for his service
in the King's private guard.

336
00:22:55.671 --> 00:22:58.334
How many men did you kill
in the Holy Land. I wonder.

337
00:22:58.408 --> 00:23:00.501
Yet here we are in Locksley.

338
00:23:00.577 --> 00:23:03.171
people that you love very much in trouble.

339
00:23:03.246 --> 00:23:05.806
and you have the chance to shoot me
but you don't take it.

340
00:23:06.683 --> 00:23:09.880
I would kill you in an instant.

341
00:23:10.954 --> 00:23:13.048
Well. maybe.

342
00:23:13.124 --> 00:23:15.819
If that was the only way
to prevent bloodshed. but...

343
00:23:18.429 --> 00:23:20.226
But it wasn't the only way. was it?

344
00:23:21.399 --> 00:23:26.803
No. you didn't have to kill me
because you could sacrifice yourself...

345
00:23:28.741 --> 00:23:30.834
and that is what you did.

346
00:23:32.411 --> 00:23:34.379
You think of me what you will.

347
00:23:35.447 --> 00:23:37.915
If I am dying tomorrow...

348
00:23:37.983 --> 00:23:39.611
it makes no difference.

349
00:23:40.285 --> 00:23:43.084
Oh. look who doesn't want to talk now.

350
00:23:45.392 --> 00:23:47.587
Jailer. open the gate.

351
00:23:52.867 --> 00:23:54.994
You're free to go.

352
00:23:55.069 --> 00:23:56.536
But I should say if you do.

353
00:23:56.604 --> 00:23:59.436
then tomorrow one or two
of your villager friends...

354
00:23:59.507 --> 00:24:02.635
Well. they won't be. how shall we say.
on speaking terms with you.

355
00:24:12.087 --> 00:24:14.647
I like it. this is good.

356
00:24:17.793 --> 00:24:23.323
I do not know why Englishmen
travel 2.000 miles to fight evil...

357
00:24:23.399 --> 00:24:25.629
when the real cancer is right here.

358
00:24:27.437 --> 00:24:29.905
Listen. I can hear a noise.
can you hear a noise?

359
00:24:31.074 --> 00:24:34.010
I think it's a dead man talking.

360
00:24:48.426 --> 00:24:49.893
I'd have gone if I were you.

361
00:24:49.961 --> 00:24:52.054
You're not me.

362
00:24:53.298 --> 00:24:58.601
(Alice) # Have you ever kissed
a boy called John?

363
00:24:58.671 --> 00:25:05.099
# For if you've never kissed
a boy called John

364
00:25:05.177 --> 00:25:08.510
# You don't know what you've missed

365
00:25:08.581 --> 00:25:13.314
# Not kissing Little John #

366
00:25:17.324 --> 00:25:19.918
(Humming)

367
00:25:36.211 --> 00:25:38.509
Think the whiney one'll make it?

368
00:25:39.781 --> 00:25:42.409
What's he gonna do?
Stroll into Nottingham and say.

369
00:25:42.483 --> 00:25:45.385
"Excuse me. can my friend
lavender boy go free?"

370
00:25:45.454 --> 00:25:47.820
Lambs to the slaughter. both of 'em.

371
00:25:48.924 --> 00:25:53.384
- Could have given him the horse.
- Then we lose a horse. too. Think about it.

372
00:25:53.462 --> 00:25:55.953
If Robin dies. the people of Locksley
will be like you.

373
00:25:56.031 --> 00:25:57.499
What do you mean "like us"?

374
00:25:57.567 --> 00:26:00.297
They'll have nothing left to live for.
They'll be dead men.

375
00:26:00.370 --> 00:26:02.965
Well. you go and save him. then. See ya!

376
00:26:03.040 --> 00:26:06.873
We don't do town. We're outlaws.
We're on the run.

377
00:26:06.943 --> 00:26:08.673
What happens to loved ones you leave?

378
00:26:08.746 --> 00:26:11.214
- Town is death.
- Have you seen what happens to a family

379
00:26:11.282 --> 00:26:14.274
- when there is only one breadwinner?
- Heartbreaking!

380
00:26:14.351 --> 00:26:17.583
Are you deaf?! We don't go to Nottingham!

381
00:26:17.655 --> 00:26:19.817
We go to Nottingham!

382
00:26:19.891 --> 00:26:22.359
(Crow caws)

383
00:26:25.463 --> 00:26:29.730
To what do we owe the pleasure
of your company. Sir Guy?

384
00:26:35.874 --> 00:26:41.438
I would be pleased if you would come
and visit me at Locksley. now that it's mine.

385
00:26:41.514 --> 00:26:43.948
I do not know.

386
00:26:44.016 --> 00:26:47.475
I have ambitions which are greater.
of course. you know that.

387
00:26:48.889 --> 00:26:52.586
But for now to have land once more
in the Gisborne name.

388
00:26:52.659 --> 00:26:54.023
my father would be proud.

389
00:26:54.094 --> 00:26:56.427
I am very glad for you.

390
00:26:56.496 --> 00:27:00.125
Some of my men. I know this for a fact.
used to laugh at my title.

391
00:27:01.335 --> 00:27:04.066
Guy of Gisborne...
when there was no Gisborne.

392
00:27:04.138 --> 00:27:06.072
And Locksley is your Gisborne?

393
00:27:07.208 --> 00:27:09.233
Yes. actually...

394
00:27:10.645 --> 00:27:12.374
I am intent on changing its name.

395
00:27:12.447 --> 00:27:14.711
Does changing a name
really make a difference?

396
00:27:14.782 --> 00:27:19.549
When a woman marries. she changes her name.
It makes a difference.

397
00:27:19.621 --> 00:27:22.147
- And what of Robin?
- What of Robin?

398
00:27:22.224 --> 00:27:25.285
He will contest your acquisition
of his lands. surely.

399
00:27:25.362 --> 00:27:28.125
- He will die.
- If he is found guilty.

400
00:27:28.197 --> 00:27:30.688
There 's no need for a trial.
He will hang in the morning.

401
00:27:30.767 --> 00:27:33.031
There must be a trial. It is the law.

402
00:27:33.103 --> 00:27:36.004
Yeah. but he is an outlaw.

403
00:27:37.475 --> 00:27:41.706
You see. in these straitened times.
the Sheriff has made special provision.

404
00:27:41.778 --> 00:27:45.111
Outlaws are classed as enemies of war.
thus we can hold them without trial.

405
00:27:45.181 --> 00:27:47.275
- No.
- And we can execute them without trial.

406
00:27:47.351 --> 00:27:48.613
No. it cannot be.

407
00:27:48.686 --> 00:27:51.120
- We're at war.
- Yes. in the Holy Land.

408
00:27:51.188 --> 00:27:53.884
That does not mean
we dispense with justice here.

409
00:27:53.958 --> 00:27:56.119
I'm sorry. I was not expecting you.

410
00:27:56.193 --> 00:27:58.992
Do not worry. Father.
Sir Guy was just leaving.

411
00:28:51.687 --> 00:28:54.154
(Dog barking)

412
00:28:54.223 --> 00:28:56.555
Shoo! Shoo!

413
00:28:57.493 --> 00:28:58.983
Go away. shoo!

414
00:29:00.097 --> 00:29:02.190
Please!

415
00:29:03.200 --> 00:29:05.167
(Cock crowing)

416
00:29:11.174 --> 00:29:13.109
(Man) Who's a good boy. eh?

417
00:29:16.781 --> 00:29:18.749
Need some help?

418
00:29:25.990 --> 00:29:27.686
Yeah. I was. er...

419
00:29:27.760 --> 00:29:30.251
I was just checking up there

420
00:29:30.329 --> 00:29:34.561
and. yes. as I thought.
the ladder is completely useless.

421
00:29:36.668 --> 00:29:39.432
Well. come on. then.

422
00:29:58.993 --> 00:30:01.188
Come on then. my lovely.

423
00:30:01.262 --> 00:30:03.025
Let's have some entertainment.

424
00:30:07.401 --> 00:30:09.392
- Where is it?
- Where is what?

425
00:30:09.470 --> 00:30:14.033
Please. the ring my father gave you years ago
before he knew the wickedness of your heart.

426
00:30:14.109 --> 00:30:18.512
Madam. I told you before.
asking doesn't usually work.

427
00:30:18.580 --> 00:30:20.173
I'll do his thumb.

428
00:30:20.249 --> 00:30:24.116
- Will those work?
- These? They're lovely.

429
00:30:24.687 --> 00:30:27.315
- When he speaks will you hear?
- Of course.

430
00:30:27.390 --> 00:30:30.621
Well. that I cannot allow.
You might get there first and steal the ring.

431
00:30:30.693 --> 00:30:33.390
Madam. I can assure you.
I'm a man of simple pleasures.

432
00:30:34.498 --> 00:30:37.126
Inflicting pain. that's enough for me.

433
00:30:37.201 --> 00:30:39.533
Maybe. but if the ring is not
where he tells me.

434
00:30:39.603 --> 00:30:42.163
suspicion will fall on you
and that would be unfair.

435
00:30:42.239 --> 00:30:45.072
- I will speak with him alone first. You may go.
- I can't do that.

436
00:30:45.142 --> 00:30:47.976
Wait outside. he cannot escape.
He will not dare attack me.

437
00:30:48.046 --> 00:30:50.014
- No. I...
- Leave.

438
00:30:51.049 --> 00:30:52.710
Yes. Your Ladyship.

439
00:30:58.556 --> 00:31:00.252
You are an utter fool.

440
00:31:00.325 --> 00:31:02.317
- You said that already.
- Oh. you listened?

441
00:31:02.394 --> 00:31:05.260
I also told you confronting
the Sheriff wouldn't work.

442
00:31:05.330 --> 00:31:07.856
- You didn't listen to that.
- I did not have much choice.

443
00:31:07.933 --> 00:31:10.697
Everything is a choice.
everything we do. Grow up.

444
00:31:10.769 --> 00:31:14.729
I prevented unjust hangings.
I protected people from my village.

445
00:31:14.808 --> 00:31:17.971
- Oh. that will make your death romantic.
- It would make it honorable.

446
00:31:18.044 --> 00:31:22.106
Honorable? And what about the people
you were so honorably protecting?

447
00:31:22.182 --> 00:31:24.515
Who will protect them when you're dead?

448
00:31:24.584 --> 00:31:27.314
Oh! What is it with men and glory?

449
00:31:27.387 --> 00:31:29.049
Glory above sense and above reason.

450
00:31:29.123 --> 00:31:31.614
- It is principle.
- Principle is making a difference

451
00:31:31.692 --> 00:31:33.523
and you can't do that if you're dead.

452
00:31:33.594 --> 00:31:37.030
You could have stayed here instead
of following your king to the Holy Land

453
00:31:37.098 --> 00:31:41.297
if you'd cared so much about
your precious people. but you didn't.

454
00:31:42.036 --> 00:31:44.129
You chose war.

455
00:31:44.205 --> 00:31:46.140
You chose glory.

456
00:31:51.813 --> 00:31:52.837
What is this about?

457
00:31:55.284 --> 00:31:58.448
It is about you saying that...

458
00:31:58.521 --> 00:32:01.649
you care about the people of Locksley.
when...

459
00:32:01.724 --> 00:32:04.818
the truth is you ran off to battle
thousands of miles away.

460
00:32:12.636 --> 00:32:14.399
You had something on your cheek.

461
00:32:20.145 --> 00:32:21.975
Right. this is what we do.

462
00:32:22.046 --> 00:32:25.539
Stand by the door. I'll scream.
in he comes. you strike him and run.

463
00:32:25.617 --> 00:32:29.314
I've paid a man by the east gate. you'll not
be seen if you leave before the day watch.

464
00:32:29.387 --> 00:32:31.288
- I cannot go unseen.
- You cannot go seen.

465
00:32:31.356 --> 00:32:34.325
- I cannot let the Sheriff win.
- Have you not heard a word I've said?

466
00:32:34.393 --> 00:32:36.725
Trust me. I have a plan.

467
00:32:36.796 --> 00:32:39.026
Well. half a plan.

468
00:32:41.667 --> 00:32:43.259
I love it when you look at me in anger.

469
00:32:43.337 --> 00:32:44.531
Oh!

470
00:32:46.205 --> 00:32:48.639
(Banging outside)

471
00:32:54.181 --> 00:32:55.648
This is a rescue.

472
00:32:59.319 --> 00:33:01.117
And we are undetected.

473
00:33:02.190 --> 00:33:04.818
(Man. shouting) In the dungeon! Outlaw!
Open this door.

474
00:33:04.892 --> 00:33:06.359
Ah!

475
00:33:07.595 --> 00:33:09.529
Oh. thank God!

476
00:33:09.597 --> 00:33:12.499
This man needs help.

477
00:33:15.871 --> 00:33:18.737
- Thank you for coming.
- Quick. before they see the open gates.

478
00:33:18.806 --> 00:33:22.106
Hang on. Hold an escape route for me.
I need five minutes.

479
00:33:22.177 --> 00:33:24.873
There 's something I must do
before I can go with you.

480
00:33:24.947 --> 00:33:28.213
- What?
- If I am longer than that. leave without me.

481
00:33:29.452 --> 00:33:31.420
- Yes.
- Thank you.

482
00:33:32.622 --> 00:33:36.490
Master. no.
You cannot go back in there.

483
00:33:36.559 --> 00:33:40.189
If you go back in and die.
then I will die. of grief.

484
00:33:41.097 --> 00:33:43.292
So you must come now. if only to save me.

485
00:33:43.367 --> 00:33:45.995
That is why I love you.

486
00:33:48.039 --> 00:33:50.337
And you... I need help.

487
00:33:50.408 --> 00:33:53.172
- It is dangerous.
- Yes.

488
00:33:58.517 --> 00:34:02.009
Why him when you love me?
Why not me?

489
00:34:05.991 --> 00:34:08.017
Here they come!

490
00:34:29.516 --> 00:34:31.643
Whoa. wait. Last man.

491
00:35:07.891 --> 00:35:12.420
Hello there! I was just passing
and the Sheriff said for me to drop in...

492
00:35:13.865 --> 00:35:14.832
at any time.

493
00:35:19.036 --> 00:35:21.470
My Lord. Robin has escaped!

494
00:35:24.041 --> 00:35:26.305
(Thud)

495
00:35:37.991 --> 00:35:38.957
What do you want?

496
00:35:39.025 --> 00:35:43.017
Yesterday in Locksley.
you revealed your true colors.

497
00:35:43.095 --> 00:35:44.221
Today. I reveal mine.

498
00:35:45.799 --> 00:35:47.164
You were right.

499
00:35:47.233 --> 00:35:49.497
I have lost my taste for bloodshed

500
00:35:49.569 --> 00:35:52.698
but if you ever callously or needlessly

501
00:35:52.772 --> 00:35:55.037
hurt anyone as a way of getting to me.

502
00:35:55.109 --> 00:35:58.670
if you cut out a tongue or brand an arm.

503
00:35:58.746 --> 00:36:02.682
or even so much as pluck the hair
of an innocent person to get to me.

504
00:36:02.750 --> 00:36:06.618
in the name of King Richard.
so help me. I will kill you.

505
00:36:10.192 --> 00:36:12.318
- I don't believe you.
- Trust me.

506
00:36:12.394 --> 00:36:14.828
What has changed since yesterday?
Nothing.

507
00:36:18.266 --> 00:36:19.597
Prove it.

508
00:36:19.668 --> 00:36:23.297
I will not change. I will stoop low. so...

509
00:36:24.073 --> 00:36:25.505
kill me now.

510
00:36:35.384 --> 00:36:37.875
Impressive.

511
00:36:37.955 --> 00:36:41.288
But each arrow that hits the wood...
Well. that is a point lost. isn't it?

512
00:36:41.758 --> 00:36:43.988
What's surprising is
you haven't even maimed me.

513
00:36:44.061 --> 00:36:47.259
I'm not even grazed.
surely I deserve at least that.

514
00:36:51.235 --> 00:36:53.329
Are you afraid of authority?

515
00:36:53.403 --> 00:36:55.771
Or is it. secretly...

516
00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:58.036
you know that I'm right?

517
00:36:58.110 --> 00:37:01.010
That we must have law and order.

518
00:37:01.079 --> 00:37:02.911
I think it is.

519
00:37:02.982 --> 00:37:07.783
I think that is why I shall
have you hang yourself.

520
00:37:11.757 --> 00:37:13.122
Now I have maimed you.

521
00:37:13.994 --> 00:37:16.019
It's a scratch. hm?

522
00:37:16.096 --> 00:37:18.064
My point. well. it still stands.

523
00:37:18.698 --> 00:37:20.757
- Lavender?
- Lavender.

524
00:37:23.536 --> 00:37:27.632
But my pain shall be salved
by a much sweeter balm.

525
00:37:27.707 --> 00:37:29.699
the knowledge that you are weak.

526
00:37:29.776 --> 00:37:34.077
As weak as your charming.
sweet conscience is strong.

527
00:37:38.053 --> 00:37:39.576
You overestimate my conscience.

528
00:37:42.256 --> 00:37:47.058
Now. do precisely as I say.
We're going to the tower.

529
00:37:49.431 --> 00:37:50.420
Stop!

530
00:37:50.933 --> 00:37:52.400
Stop!

531
00:37:53.302 --> 00:37:55.634
Do not harm those men. they're free to go.

532
00:37:55.704 --> 00:37:57.673
I have an announcement to make.

533
00:37:57.739 --> 00:37:59.207
- I.
- I...

534
00:37:59.275 --> 00:38:00.799
Vaizey. Sheriff of Nottingham...

535
00:38:00.877 --> 00:38:04.005
- In recognition.
...in recognition...

536
00:38:04.080 --> 00:38:06.344
- Of my.
...of my...

537
00:38:06.416 --> 00:38:09.750
illegal actions yesterday in Locksley...

538
00:38:09.819 --> 00:38:13.085
- Do humbly apologize.
...do humbly apologize...

539
00:38:13.157 --> 00:38:18.686
to the innocent people
who have suffered at my hands.

540
00:38:18.762 --> 00:38:21.732
I promise to pay 500 pounds.

541
00:38:21.800 --> 00:38:24.563
I promise to pay...

542
00:38:26.171 --> 00:38:29.140
No! No. I cannot go on.

543
00:38:29.208 --> 00:38:31.038
You will have to kill...

544
00:38:31.109 --> 00:38:33.635
Guards! Guards!

545
00:38:33.713 --> 00:38:34.941
Stop those men!

546
00:39:00.040 --> 00:39:01.736
Much! Much!

547
00:39:02.810 --> 00:39:04.504
And shoot Locksley!

548
00:39:15.991 --> 00:39:17.754
Much!

549
00:39:20.362 --> 00:39:22.626
Tie this off.

550
00:39:30.840 --> 00:39:32.500
Robin. where?

551
00:39:32.575 --> 00:39:33.735
Here!

552
00:39:41.217 --> 00:39:43.242
- You. defend me.
- Me?

553
00:39:43.888 --> 00:39:45.219
(Little John) Yes!

554
00:39:50.761 --> 00:39:51.887
Yes!

555
00:40:15.054 --> 00:40:17.488
- That arrow hurt. lavender boy!
- Heartbreaking.

556
00:40:23.730 --> 00:40:25.129
Ready?

557
00:40:26.166 --> 00:40:27.633
Go!

558
00:40:46.821 --> 00:40:49.552
(Cheering)

559
00:41:13.784 --> 00:41:15.217
That her?

560
00:41:15.286 --> 00:41:17.254
(Allan) She's your wife?

561
00:41:18.155 --> 00:41:20.385
What does she see in you?

562
00:41:20.458 --> 00:41:22.653
(Forrest) Look. she's seen it. Look!

563
00:41:32.905 --> 00:41:35.897
- That is good.
- Yeah.

564
00:42:00.067 --> 00:42:01.500
Come on!

565
00:42:22.490 --> 00:42:26.154
You know. I myself.
have no family at all. of course.

566
00:42:26.229 --> 00:42:27.719
No family.

567
00:42:28.297 --> 00:42:31.425
No wife. children.

568
00:42:31.500 --> 00:42:35.096
Strangely. it doesn't bother me.
Not at all.

569
00:42:36.206 --> 00:42:37.673
Not at all.

570
00:42:42.946 --> 00:42:44.345
Mm...

571
00:42:44.414 --> 00:42:47.042
Excuse me. I think you'll find
that's not properly cooked.

572
00:42:56.761 --> 00:42:58.729
Very funny.

573
00:42:59.305 --> 00:43:59.164
